<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"  TextAlignment="Justify"   xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml">

<Paragraph>Essential Presentation library has support for merging two presentation documents into one.</Paragraph>
<Paragraph>This sample demonstrates merging two PowerPoint presentation documents with paste options - use destination theme and source formatting.</Paragraph>
<BlockUIContainer>
<TextBlock Style="{DynamicResource HeaderTextStyle}"><Bold>Features:</Bold></TextBlock>
</BlockUIContainer>
<List>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Copied slides can be merged with 'source' or 'destination' paste options equivalent to Microsoft PowerPoint.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Merge an entire presentation with another Presentation by merging all the copied slides of the presentation to another.</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>
<Paragraph>Note: This library supports creation, manipulation and conversion to PDF/image for .pptx format alone.</Paragraph>
